{
  "stem": "1502.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there were times that they would give Jewish mothers the alternative to let the children be taken away by the Judenrat and placed into homes.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there was a number of Jewish children in these homes.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "These homes were run by the Judenrat, and they were employees in these homes, Jewish young men and girls.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "These people that worked in the homes had a so-called protection of being deported as long as they worked there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The idea why they did it is, some people, there was a rumor, that the queen, that the mother queen, Belgium was a kingdom, the king of Belgium at that time was a collaborator.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "After the war, he was banished from Belgium.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But his mother was trying to help Jews.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And apparently, it was through her intervention that they established these few homes for some of the children.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now, whoever was lucky enough and whichever mother had the foresight to give the child to them, they saved, that child would have been saved.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They also had, even saw that they-- they deported thousands of elderly Jews from Belgium.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They made an old age home.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they would take, there were no rules by them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "One day they would do this, and the next day they would do something different.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And sometimes when they caught elderly Jews, they would send them to the old age home, which at the end of the war, had a few hundred elderly Jews.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "What we figured out, the reason why they did this, is because the Gestapo people that were handling the Jewish section had it very good in Belgium.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They had a type of life that they couldn't have in Germany.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They lived in luxury.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they wanted to extend for themselves just as long as possible.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
